review_blob: Bomber poured into a snifter -- Aroma is malty and pleasant, beer appears dark with no head. Flavor is sweet berry and sweet malt with a tint of alcohol. Aftertaste is mostly lingering sweetness, not quite cloying and not quite balanced. Okay overall, but I wonder how this would be with some age on it.
beer_name: New Belgium Lips of Faith - Blackberry Barleywine

review_blob: Thanks to oldrtybastrd for the can -- poured into a snifter. Active carbonation upon pouring. Clear dark caramel colored brew with no head. Malty and boozey aroma. Flavor is Belgian fermented malt, slight hop bitterness. Very nice beer.
Bottle from Surdyks -- poured into a snifter, not overly impressed by the base stout, a little weak. The barrel shined, however, great oaky and whisky notes. Awesome label art.
beer_name: Bent Brewstillery Dark Fatha Barrel Aged

review_blob: Drank before my first concert in Minot. Pretty well crafted pale ale, great malt profile to highlight the Simcoe hops. Hops shine through extremely well.
UPDATED: APR 14, 2016
From 19 Mar 2016 -- Good malt backbone. The hops just arent enough for me. Meh.

500mL poured into a tulip -- beautiful beer, opaque brown with one inch head that doesnt stop. Roasty malts accented nicely by Prairies Saison yeast. Pleasant drinker fit those that love darker brews.
Great Aroma, great color, great malt backbone for the hops. Not very hoppy in the flavor though.
Bottle poured into a snifter -- Good beginner sour. Some Brett funk and just a little bit of tartness. Curious how this would taste with some time on it.
Bottle poured into a snifter -- definitely can taste the barrel. Didnt realize this was a 12%er.
On tap on St Pattys Day at the brewery -- this is a great smoked beer. Great flavor subtle smoke, just great.
Beer sample on the surly brewery tour -- great helles, good clarity, color, aroma and flavor. Malty and delish.
St Pattys brew on tap at Surly. Good and interesting cranberry stout. Would drink again.
Was very happy how fast I could find this beer, and on St Pattys Day! Great stout with hints of smoke and peat!
beer_name: Clown Shoes Flight of the Angry Beast

review_blob: St Pattys Day -- on tap. Great sour brown. Can taste a hint of barrel and that adds a great level of complexity.
First beer of St Pattys Day -- on tap. A little sweet, but unbeknownst to me, it was an 8% beer so it makes sense. Otherwise a very nice beer.
beer_name: Indeed Derailed  #2 - Mexican Honey Imperial Lager

review_blob: Bottle shared while at the Gabriel household for the weekend -- Good malty Lager, better than BMC swill.
On tap -- the base beer doesnt quite hold up to the Bourbon Barrel. The barrel shines, and I love its flavors.
beer_name: Local Option / Central Waters De Kleine Dood

review_blob: On tap -- tastes like a mix between a dubbel and a porter. Not quite "olde" enough.
Bottle poured into a glass -- I cant believe Ive never rated this. Great aroma, nice clean enjoyable beer.
beer_name: Lagunitas A Little Sumpin Sumpin Ale

review_blob: Bottle poured into a tulip -- That is a great sour. Very tart and the agave really helps the flavor and accents the beer perfectly.
beer_name: Avery Barrel-Aged Series 26 - Tectum et Elix

review_blob: From the bottle poured into a pint glass -- very meh. Completely unremarkable. Wont seek out again.
Really good California Common. Great color, awesome malt backbone with just enough dryness.
Beautiful color, great nose, perfect mouthfeel. Flavor, though, is lacking. Could up the flavor hops to give it more.
Not a super tart or super salty, but a good looking easy to drink Gose. Enjoyable albeit a little unremarkable.

On tap at the brewery; served in a pint glass -- Translucent Ruby color, pretty awesome lacing. Aroma is okay. Flavor makes up for it and strong malt followed by pine. Flavor is good malt but really pronounced hops.

First beer back from deployment! Its good to be back and SRB does not disappoint the homecoming. This is a great Saison base with a hint of tartness that really adds a little zing to it. I really enjoy this one.
Just recently had on tap at the brewery. Its a straw colored very clear beer. Aroma is a hint of pineapple almost masked by the acidity of the beer. Its pretty good for SRBs first sour.
12oz bottle poured into a pint glass -- Aroma is super malty, looks like a hazy amber color. Taste is a malty bitterness that is quite pleasant. Yeah, this drinks quite well. (bottle says 12%abv)
beer_name: Dark Horse Double Crooked Tree IPA

review_blob: Part of a flight I had at the brewpub -- Pretty good red. On the dry and roasty side, in a good way. Quite enjoyable.
beer_name: Great Deep Dos Amantes Irish Red Ale

review_blob: Part of a flight I had at the brewpub -- A very light beer. Some aromatics of tropical hops, but muted. Flavor was very light. The sessionability of this beer is what made it good.
Part of a flight I had at the brewpub -- My least favorite of the flight. It was sweet and the sweetness wasnt very well balanced. Also, I wish it had more rye spiciness.
beer_name: Great Deep Chelu Honey Rye Brown Ale

review_blob: Part of a flight I had at the brewpub -- A hazy golden to orange color. Nice subtle tropical fruit aromas. Flavor had a firm bitterness that gave the other hop flavors a good backbone. Very enjoyable, probably my favorite of the flight.
beer_name: Great Deep Manhita India Pale Ale

review_blob: Part of a flight I had at the brewpub -- Looked very appealing. Upon tasting I was a little disappointed, it was slightly thin and didnt have the mouthfeel of most typical oatmeal stouts. Otherwise it was a very good beer.

Went searching for the brewery, extremely small operation, but the owners were very nice. Sampled this at the brewery -- poured into an Ishii pint glass. Aroma was smokey and dark. The flavor was peatey, smokey, and delicious.
Bottle poured into my Waikikis hotel glass -- It wasnt an overly aromatic IPA, but it was a solid drinking beer. I enjoyed the entire bottle.

Brought back to ND from OK by Craig and shared -- Stubby bottle poured into a Prairie 2nd Anniversary teku. It pours black with a mocha ring of head around the glass. Aroma is burnt sugar coconut and rich malt. Flavor is dark sugar, caramel; smooth and rich. Flavors cascade in your mouth with varying degrees of sweetness and depth. Darn good beer.

Bottle received in a trade, thanks Brandon! -- Bomber poured into a snifter. Its a beautiful copper with blue/purple colors throughout. Nice sour and tartness, not overpowering. Finishes well, makes you want more.
beer_name: New Holland Barrel Aged Blue Sunday 13 (2010 - * )

review_blob: Received from my Summer Secret Santa! Can poured into a snifter -- Pours a cloudy straw yellow. Smells tart. Flavor is awesome. I shared this with four folks and they all loved it. Its a great smooth Berliner.

Bottle thanks to my Oklahoma sister! 750mL bottle poured into a snifter -- Citra all the way. For a Brett beer this is super malty. Holy crap, its 10%. Im really wondering how this would change with a year or more on it.
beer_name: The Willows Family Ales Funk in the Trunk

review_blob: Rated based on notes taken 11 Nov 2012 -- This beer surprised me. I was expecting a crappy fruit beer. Instead its a decent fruit beer. The prickly pear comes through pretty well in the nose and theres just a hint of it in the flavor. Wish there was more, but not bad.
Rated based on notes taken 11 Nov 2012 -- Not impressed with this beer. Just a step above the crappy American Lagers.

beer_brewer_name: Vermont Hard Cider Company, LLC (C&C; Group)
review_blob: Rated based on notes taken 10 Nov 2012 -- Its a cider. It tastes summer-y? Not bad, not good.
Rated based on notes taken 6 Nov 2012 -- The barrel aged wine flavor adds a unique layer. Definitely interesting.
Rated based on notes taken 4 Nov 2012 -- Drank at the Alamo Theater, San Antonio. Dang good Wit. Interesting choice to turn into a double-version. Turned out pretty good though.
beer_name: Boulevard Smokestack Series - Two Jokers Double-Wit

review_blob: Rated based on notes taken 3 Nov 2012 -- On tap at the Dia de la Muerta release party at the Brewery! Bottle share at the party! Didnt get a picture or write down what batch this was, but it was pre-16. Great beer, quite a bit different from the La Muerta I was drinking at the release, creamier and more attenuated.
beer_name: Jester King Black Metal Farmhouse Imperial Stout

review_blob: Rated based on notes taken 3 Nov 2012 -- On tap at the Dia de la Muerta release party at the Brewery! Good IPA, not as good as the Hopothesis. Solid.

Rated based on notes taken 3 Nov 2012 -- On tap at the Dia de la Muerta release party at the Brewery! Great Sour. Its important to note that Freetail produced the first sours that I tried. Ive come a long way.
Rated based on notes taken 3 Nov 2012 -- On tap at the Dia de la Muerta release party at the Brewery! A-mazing IPA. Out of this world citris aroma, amazing malt flavor!
Rated based on notes taken 3 Nov 2012 -- On tap at the Dia de la Muerta release party at the Brewery! Great time and an awesome beer. Suuuuuper smooth. Rounds the beer out nicely.
